  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nLighthouse attestations are failing per beaconcha.in\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nPlease provide your Lighthouse and Rust version. Are you building from\r\n`stable` or `unstable`, which commit?\r\n\r\nLighthouse version 1.3.0 and the latest version of rust (as of today)\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nI am running lighhouse on an ubuntu 20.04 server with 6 GB RAM and 150 GB SSD. (I am using infura for eth1) It has been working fine since Dec2020, but the attestations started failing last week. Today I updated lighhouse from 1.02 to 1.3.0 this morning and I dont see any errors in the syslog - but the beaconcha.in is still reporting attestations are failing.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nThe Attestations should not fail.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nPlease describe the steps required to resolve this issue, if known.\r\n",
